      {
        "title": "Infrastructure Control and Management",
        "content": "On-Premises:\n*   Complete control over hardware, software, and data.\n*   Organizations are responsible for all aspects of IT infrastructure management, including maintenance, upgrades, and security.\n\nCloud:\n*   Shared control model; AWS manages the underlying infrastructure.\n*   You manage applications, data, and configurations within the cloud environment.\n*   Reduces operational overhead and allows focus on core business activities."
      },
      {
        "title": "Scalability and Elasticity",
        "content": "On-Premises:\n*   Scalability is limited by physical hardware capacity.\n*   Scaling up requires significant capital expenditure and lead time for procurement and installation.\n\nCloud:\n*   Highly scalable and elastic; resources can be provisioned and de-provisioned on demand.\n*   Pay-as-you-go model optimizes cost by only paying for resources consumed.\n*   Supports rapid scaling to meet fluctuating demands without long-term commitments."
      },
      {
        "title": "Cost and Operational Expenditure",
        "content": "On-Premises:\n*   High upfront capital expenditure (CapEx) for hardware, software, and infrastructure.\n*   Ongoing operational expenditure (OpEx) for maintenance, power, cooling, and IT staff.\n\nCloud:\n*   Minimal upfront investment; primarily operational expenditure (OpEx).\n*   Reduces costs associated with hardware maintenance, data center operations, and IT staffing.\n*   Offers predictable pricing models and cost optimization tools to manage cloud spending effectively."
      }
    ]
  }
}
